<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="suppose-vt">suppose <strong><em>vt</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /sə'pəʊz/    美 /sə'poʊz/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>认为；猜想</strong></h4>
<p>to think that sth is probable：</p>
<ul>
<li>suppose (that) …:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I suppose (that) price will go up. 
我认为价格会上涨。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Will it rain tomorrow? 
明天会下雨吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— I suppose so. / I suppose not. 
我想会/我想不会。</p></div>

<p>注: 常用so或not来代替that从句进行回答。<br />
- I don’t suppose (that) …:</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I don’t suppose anyone will volunteer, will they? 
我觉得没有人会自告奋勇，是不是？</p></div>

<p>注: suppose后的that从句的否定形式通常转移到 suppose上。主句主语是I时，反意疑问句仍然跟从句相关，且用肯定形式。<br />
- When / Why / What / … do you suppose …?</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When do you suppose we should leave? 
你认为我们应该什么时候动身？</p></div>

<p>注: 上例中，when should we leave用陈述句式。<br />
- suppose ... to be / to do sth:</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I shall suppose him to be about fifty. 
我想他应该在50岁左右。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We suppose them to have finished their homework.
我们想他们已经完成作业了。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>suppose ... + adj / n:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She had supposed him (to be) very rich. 
她原以为他很有钱。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I had supposed his wife a younger woman. 
我原以为他的妻子更年轻。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>假定；假设</strong></h4>
<p>to pretend that sth will happen or is true：</p>
<ul>
<li>suppose (that) …:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Suppose (that) you have one million dollars — what would you do? 
假如你有一百万美金，你会做什么？</p></div>

<ul>
<li>suppose ... to be / to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Let’s suppose the old woman to be your mother. 
我们假定那位老妇人是你的母亲。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>suppose ... + adj / n:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Suppose the hero dead — what then？
假设男主角死了，那怎么办？</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>[表示婉转提建议或勉强同意]：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Suppose we go for a swim. 
咱们去游泳吧。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Can I borrow the car? 
我能借车一用吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Oh, <strong>I suppose so</strong>. 
噢，可以吧。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="be-supposed-to-be-to-do-sth">(be) supposed to be / to do sth</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>被认为；被当作：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I haven’t seen it myself, but it is supposed to be a great movie. 
我没看过这部电影，但是据说很不错。</p></div>

<p>2.★ <strong>应该；理应：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The college years are supposed to be a time for important growth in dependence.
大学期间应是培养独立性的重要时期。</p><footer>2016 北京改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You’re not supposed to smoke here. 
这里不可以吸烟。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>What are you doing out of bed, Tom? You’re s<strong><em>_</em></strong>__ to be asleep.   （2011 辽宁改）  </li>
<li>The message is very important, so it is supposed <strong><em>_</em></strong>___ (send) as soon as possible.  （2008 陕西改）  </li>
<li>— You should apologize to her, Barry.
— I suppose <strong><em>_</em></strong>__, but it’s not going to be easy.   </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. supposed  2. to be sent   3. so  </p></div>